===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – a tall building (i.e. a tower). Compare {{zh-l|*高}}.

When used as a component on top of the character, the character loses the bottom part {{zh-l|*小}}. (e.g., {{zh-l|*亮}} and {{zh-l|*亭}}).

===Etymology 1===
Either from:
* {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-gaŋ||hill, ridge, mountain}} (STEDT), cognate with {{och-l|岡|hill, crest}}, {{och-l|鯨|whale}}, {{cog|bo|སྒང༌||ridge; mound}}, {{cog|my|ခင်||ridge}}, {{cog|my|အခေါင်||summit}}, {{cog|lhu|qhɔ³³||mountain}}, {{cog|suv|gɹaŋ³³||mountain}}, Proto-{{w|Tamangic languages|Tamangic}} *''ᴬgaŋ'' ("hill, mountain"); or
* of {{der|zh|aav}} origin, compare {{cog|mkh-pro|*graŋ||hill, peak}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), whence {{cog|mnw|ဂြၚ်|tr=krɛ̀aŋ|t=peak}} and {{cog|okz|grāṅ||hill on flat land}}.

Within Chinese, cognate with {{och-l|景|large}}, {{och-l|鯨|whale}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

